{"title_page": "Meaghan Rath", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2014}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name         = Meaghan Rath\n| birth_name   =\n| birth_date   = {{birth date and age|1986|06|18}}\n| birth_place  = [[Montreal]], [[Quebec]], Canada\n| image        = Meaghan Rath of Being Human at Wizard World Toronto 2012.jpg\n| caption      = Rath at Wizard World [[Toronto Comic Con]] in 2012\n| other_names  =\n| years_active = 2001\u2013present\n| spouse       =\n| relatives    = [[Jesse Rath]] {{small|(brother)}}\n| occupation   = Actress\n}}\n\n'''Meaghan Rath''' (born June 18, 1986) is a Canadian film and television actress. She is known for her television roles on ''[[Being Human (North American TV series)|Being Human]]'', ''[[15/Love]]'', ''[[The Assistants]]'', [[Banshee (TV series)|Banshee]] and ''[[Hawaii Five-0 (2010 TV series)|Hawaii Five-0]]''.\n\n==Personal life ==\nRath was born in [[Montreal]], [[Quebec]]. Her mother is of Indian origin, whereas her father is of [[English Jew|English Jewish]] and [[Austrian Jewish]] descent. She has a younger brother, [[Jesse Rath]], who is also an actor.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ca.complex.com/pop-culture/2014/01/meaghan-rath-being-human-interview/meaghan-rath-being-human-character-reflects-her|title=How Sally is a Lot Like Meaghan - Personality Complex: \"Being Human\" Star Meaghan Rath Loves How You're Underestimating Her - Complex CA|author=Matt Barone|work=Complex CA}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://montrealgazette.com/entertainment/local-arts/on-the-scene-of-the-crime-and-comedy-romance-and-sci-fi|title=On the scene of the crime \u2014 and comedy, romance and sci-fi|author=Bill Brownstein, Montreal Gazette More Bill Brownstein, Montreal Gazette|work=Montreal Gazette}}</ref>  She studied Cinema and Communications at [[Dawson College]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://americanprofile.com/articles/about-meaghan-rath-of-being-human/|title=About Meaghan Rath of 'Being Human'|author=Paulette Cohn|publisher=americanprofile.com}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2001\n| ''[[Lost and Delirious]]''\n| Allison's Friend #3\n| \n|-\n| 2008\n| ''Prom Wars: Love Is a Battlefield''\n| Jen L.\n| \n|-\n| 2010\n| ''You Are So Undead''\n| Mary Margaret\n| Short film\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''Three Night Stand''\n| Sue\n| Also executive producer\n|-\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2004\n| ''[[Fries with That?]]''\n| Customer/Molly\n| 2 episodes\n|-\n| 2006\n| ''[[10.5: Apocalypse]]''\n| Rachel\n| Television miniseries\n|-\n| 2004\u20132006\n| ''[[15/Love]]''\n| Adena Stiles\n| Main role\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[I Me Wed]]''\n| Tracy\n| Television film\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''My Daughter's Secret''\n| Courtney\n| Television film\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[Heartland (Canadian TV series)|Heartland]]''\n| Jen\n| Episode: \"Coming Home\"\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[Aaron Stone]]''\n| Tatianna Caine\n| 2 episodes\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''{{sortname|The|Assistants}}''\n| Rigby Hastings\n| Main role\n|-\n| 2010\u20132011\n| ''[[18 to Life]]''\n| Violet/Erin Boyd\n| 2 episodes\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''[[Cyberbully (2011 film)|Cyberbully]]''\n| Cheyenne Mortenson\n| Television film\n|-\n| 2011\u20132014\n| ''[[Being Human (North American TV series)|Being Human]]''\n| [[List of Being Human (North American TV series) characters#Sally Malik|Sally Malik]]\n| Main role\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[Flashpoint (TV series)|Flashpoint]]''\n| Rebecca Vaughan\n| Episode: \"Eyes In\"\n|-\n| 2014 \n| ''[[Kingdom (2014 TV series)|Kingdom]]''\n| Tatiana\n| 3 episodes\n|-\n| 2015\u20132016\n| ''[[New Girl]]''\n| [[List of New Girl characters#May|May]] \n| Recurring role (seasons 4\u20135), 5 episodes\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''[[Banshee (TV series)|Banshee]]''\n| Aimee King\n| Recurring role (season 3), 5 episodes\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''[[Secrets and Lies (U.S. TV series)|Secrets and Lies]]''\n| Nicole Mullen\n| Recurring role, 5 episodes\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''[[Motive (TV series)|Motive]]''\n| Ella Rollins\n| Episode: \"The Suicide Tree\"\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Cooper Barrett's Guide to Surviving Life]]''\n| Kelly Bishop\n| Main role\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Rogue (TV series)|Rogue]]''\n| Clea Annou\n| Main role (season 4)\n|-\n| 2017\u20132020\n| ''[[Hawaii Five-0 (2010 TV series)|Hawaii Five-0]]''\n| Tani Rey \n| Main role (season 8\u201310)\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''[[Schitt's Creek]]''\n| Klair\n| Episode: \"Baby Sprinkle\"\n|-\n| 2020\n| ''[[Magnum P.I. (2018 TV series)|Magnum P.I.]]''\n| Tani Rey\n| Episode: \"Desperate Measures\"\n|-\n| 2020\n| ''[[Supergirl (TV series)|Supergirl]]''\n| Female Brainiac-5\n| Episode: \"The Bottle Episode\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://comicbook.com/dc/2019/07/21/supergirl-season-5-meaghan-rath-female-brainiac-5-sdcc/|title=Supergirl: Meaghan Rath to Play a Female Brainiac 5|website=DC|language=en|access-date=2020-01-08}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Award\n! scope=\"col\" | Category\n! scope=\"col\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" | Result\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | {{abbr|Ref.|References}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 2015\n| [[Golden Maple Award]]\n| Newcomer of the Year in a TV Series Broadcast in the U.S.\n| ''[[New Girl]]''\n| {{Won}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref>{{cite web|last=Levine|first=Sydney|title=Golden Maple Awards '15 Winners Include Brandon Jay McLaren and Amanda Crew |url=http://www.indiewire.com/2015/07/golden-maple-awards15-winners-include-brandon-jay-mclaren-and-amanda-crew-171061/|publisher=IndieWire|access-date=November 12, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | 2017\n| [[Leo Award]]\n| Best Lead Performance by a Female in a Dramatic Series\n| ''[[Rogue (TV series)|Rogue]]''\n| {{Nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref>{{cite web|title=Leo Awards, Nominees by Name 2017|url=http://www.leoawards.com/2017/nominees/by_name.php|publisher=Leo Awards|access-date=May 2, 2017|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170527200921/http://www.leoawards.com/2017/nominees/by_name.php|archivedate=May 27, 2017}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Twitter}}\n*{{IMDb name|1012010}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Rath, Meaghan}}\n\n[[Category:1986 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century Canadian actresses]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Montreal]]\n[[Category:Anglophone Quebec people]]\n[[Category:Canadian actresses of Indian descent]]\n[[Category:Canadian child actresses]]\n[[Category:Canadian film actresses]]\n[[Category:Canadian people of Austrian-Jewish descent]]\n[[Category:Canadian people of British descent]]\n[[Category:Canadian television actresses]]\n[[Category:Dawson College alumni]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2014}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name         = Meaghan Rath\n| birth_name   =\n| birth_date   = {{birth date and age|1986|06|18}}\n| birth_place  = [[Montreal]], [[Quebec]], Canada\n| image        = Meaghan Rath of Being Human at Wizard World Toronto 2012.jpg\n| caption      = Rath at Wizard World [[Toronto Comic Con]] in 2012\n| other_names  =\n| years_active = 2001\u2013present\n| spouse       =\n| relatives    = [[Jesse Rath]] {{small|(brother)}}\n| occupation   = Actress\n}}\n\n'''Meaghan Rath''' (born June 18, 1986) is a Canadian film and television actress. She is known for her television roles on ''[[Being Human (North American TV series)|Being Human]]'', ''[[15/Love]]'', ''[[The Assistants]]'', and ''[[Hawaii Five-0 (2010 TV series)|Hawaii Five-0]]''.\n\n==Personal life ==\nRath was born in [[Montreal]], [[Quebec]]. Her mother is of Indian origin, whereas her father is of [[English Jew|English Jewish]] and [[Austrian Jewish]] descent. She has a younger brother, [[Jesse Rath]], who is also an actor.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ca.complex.com/pop-culture/2014/01/meaghan-rath-being-human-interview/meaghan-rath-being-human-character-reflects-her|title=How Sally is a Lot Like Meaghan - Personality Complex: \"Being Human\" Star Meaghan Rath Loves How You're Underestimating Her - Complex CA|author=Matt Barone|work=Complex CA}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://montrealgazette.com/entertainment/local-arts/on-the-scene-of-the-crime-and-comedy-romance-and-sci-fi|title=On the scene of the crime \u2014 and comedy, romance and sci-fi|author=Bill Brownstein, Montreal Gazette More Bill Brownstein, Montreal Gazette|work=Montreal Gazette}}</ref>  She studied Cinema and Communications at [[Dawson College]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://americanprofile.com/articles/about-meaghan-rath-of-being-human/|title=About Meaghan Rath of 'Being Human'|author=Paulette Cohn|publisher=americanprofile.com}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2001\n| ''[[Lost and Delirious]]''\n| Allison's Friend #3\n| \n|-\n| 2008\n| ''Prom Wars: Love Is a Battlefield''\n| Jen L.\n| \n|-\n| 2010\n| ''You Are So Undead''\n| Mary Margaret\n| Short film\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''Three Night Stand''\n| Sue\n| Also executive producer\n|-\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2004\n| ''[[Fries with That?]]''\n| Customer/Molly\n| 2 episodes\n|-\n| 2006\n| ''[[10.5: Apocalypse]]''\n| Rachel\n| Television miniseries\n|-\n| 2004\u20132006\n| ''[[15/Love]]''\n| Adena Stiles\n| Main role\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[I Me Wed]]''\n| Tracy\n| Television film\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''My Daughter's Secret''\n| Courtney\n| Television film\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[Heartland (Canadian TV series)|Heartland]]''\n| Jen\n| Episode: \"Coming Home\"\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[Aaron Stone]]''\n| Tatianna Caine\n| 2 episodes\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''{{sortname|The|Assistants}}''\n| Rigby Hastings\n| Main role\n|-\n| 2010\u20132011\n| ''[[18 to Life]]''\n| Violet/Erin Boyd\n| 2